    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.03746.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">1437 So. Broad</name>
                    <date when="1886-09-16">9.<hi rend="underline">16th</hi> 86</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Walt Whitman</salute>
                <salute>My Dear Old Friend</salute>
            </opener>
            <p> You must drive out and see us as soon as you&#8212;dinner 6 pm. </p>
            <p>
                <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#ss" cert="low">Mrs Pearce</unclear> is still in
                Brooklyn with her sister Mrs Dean&#8212; </p>
            <p> The children are happy as crickets &#38; all say "we will miss Walt &#38; the old
                    <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.03746.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/> "fire in the
                low down grate"&#8212; </p>
            <p> Not a coal from the house d&#8212;n it all <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#ss"
                    cert="low">heating</unclear>. Sewell &#38; I have made up. <hi rend="underline"
                    >He</hi> sent for me Monday&#8212;I went. I will soon have some money &#38; will
                    <hi rend="underline">square up</hi> thanks to you Dear old friend. </p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours</salute>
                <signed>James Scovel</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>Regards to Mrs Davis</p>
            </postscript>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.03746.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
            <note type="authorial"> Let me know when you write anything new JWS </note>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.03746.004_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
